&lt;td&gt;Thus [is] the rule of these: if to the [usually] recited three &lt;i&gt;sūtra&lt;/i&gt;s one says [something] in reply [for]ever, the text becomes [too] large. That is why we do not say it.&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;684&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;a2&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;If by nature there were experiences of happiness and sorrow, how is the experience of indifference to be understood?&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;320&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;a3-4&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;When these experiences are not there in the mind, there is certainly indifference.&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;317&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
